<refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="immeanshift" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org">
<refnamediv><refname>immeanshift</refname><refpurpose>Apply iterative mean-shift-like smoothing.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = immeanshift(image)
out = immeanshift(image, spatialRadius, colorRadius, iterations)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input grayscale or RGB image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>spatialRadius</term><listitem><para>Spatial smoothing radius in pixels. Default is <literal>5</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>colorRadius</term><listitem><para>Intensity/color radius controlling update strength. Default is <literal>0.1</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>iterations</term><listitem><para>Positive iteration count. Default is <literal>3</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Smoothed double image clipped to <literal>[0, 1]</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Uses iterative Gaussian local means with color-distance weighting. Output is double-valued in the range 0 to 1.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_fruits.jpg"));
image = imresize(image, [120 160]);
out = immeanshift(image, 5, 0.1, 3);
subplot(1, 2, 1);
imshow(image);
subplot(1, 2, 2);
imshow(out);]]></programlisting></refsection>
